                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>CHRISTIAN BERGSTROM. On the 15th of March the prisoner came to my shop in <placeName id="t18300415-204-crimeloc1137">Tottenham-court-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-204-crimeloc1137" type="placeName" value="Tottenham-court-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-204-crimeloc1137" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-204-off1136 t18300415-204-crimeloc1137"></join>, under pretence of buying an umbrella; he went out of the shop- I followed him, and found this umbrella and stick on him; he would not give them up - a gentleman went for an officer; he was but a few yards from the shop when I took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-204-person1820">
                  MATTHEW 
                  LOVEDAY
               <interp inst="t18300415-204-person1820" type="surname" value="LOVEDAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-204-person1820" type="given" value="MATTHEW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-204-person1820" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and took him; he made a great resistance - I was obliged to throw him on the ground, and take him by force; I found some copper money on him.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that the prosecutor had given the things into his hand, and that the officer had ill-treated him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-204-person1821">
                  CHRISTIAN 
                  BERGSTROM
               <interp inst="t18300415-204-person1821" type="surname" value="BERGSTROM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-204-person1821" type="given" value="CHRISTIAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-204-person1821" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I did not sell them, or give them to him; he did not say he wanted to take them any where.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I asked the price, and he said 5s.; I disputed it, and he said I might have it for 4s. - I said if he would come himself, or send his shopman, to King's Headcourt, I would give him an answer - I have been cupped and blistered at the hospital for a brain fever.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-204-verdict1138" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-204-verdict1138" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 23. - <rs id="t18300415-204-punish1139" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-204-punish1139" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-204-defend1817 t18300415-204-punish1139"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
